{
  "page": "Aegon's Conquest (TV series)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">This article is about the planned television series. For the conquest of Westeros, see <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>. For the chapter, see <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest_(Fire_%26_Blood)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest (Fire &amp; Blood)\">Aegon's Conquest (Fire &amp; Blood)</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary navbox-title\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-style: italic; background-color:&#91;&#91;:Template:Infobox television/colour&#93;&#93;;\">Aegon's Conquest</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fantasy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fantasy\">Fantasy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Developed by</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mattson_Tomlin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mattson Tomlin\">Mattson Tomlin</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Tomlin_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Tomlin-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Written by</th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mattson_Tomlin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mattson Tomlin\">Mattson Tomlin</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country of origin</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language(s)</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Production <span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">company(s)</span></th><td>\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HBO\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:HBO\">HBO</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"navbox-title\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:&#91;&#91;:Template:Infobox television/colour&#93;&#93;;\">Chronology</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Related shows</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A live-action American <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fantasy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Fantasy\">fantasy</a> television series based on <b>Aegon's Conquest</b> is being discussed at HBO. The series would take place three hundred years before the events of <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i>, and would explore the story of the <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">conquest</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> and his sisters, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen\">Rhaenys</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Visenya_Targaryen\" title=\"Visenya Targaryen\">Visenya</a>.\n</p><p>Discussion of this project was first rumored in April 2023,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Variety_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Variety-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> but confirmation came on February 9, 2024, when it was revealed that screenwriter <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mattson_Tomlin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mattson Tomlin\">Mattson Tomlin</a> is attached to lead the project. It is still in the pitch phase, and has not been officially greenlit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Tomlin_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Tomlin-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The working title of the series is not yet known.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Aegon%27s_Conquest_(TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Aegon%27s_Conquest_(Rand_Ravich/Far_Shariat)\">first attempt</a> to pitch a prequel about Aegon's Conquest was made in 2017. In summer 2017, HBO announced that five separate prequel pitches were under consideration, none of which were ultimately greenlit. One, by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rand_Ravich\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Rand Ravich\">Rand Ravich</a> and <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Far_Shariat\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Far Shariat\">Far Shariat</a>, was about Aegon's Conquest. Their script portrayed Aegon the Conqueror as \"a drunken lout,\" and was one of the first pitches rejected by HBO.<sup id=\"cite_ref-THR_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-THR-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On April 3, 2023, <i>Variety</i> revealed that a new prequel about Aegon's Conquest was being considered by HBO. Early talks suggested the potential for a feature component to the project, in which HBO and Warner Bros. could release a theatrical film that would lead directly into the series. No writer was mentioned as being attached to the project at the time.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Variety_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Variety-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Following the straight-to-series order for <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Knight_of_the_Seven_Kingdoms_(TV_series)\" title=\"A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms (TV series)\">A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms</a></i>, then titled <i>A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms: The Hedge Knight</i>, on April 12, 2023, <i>Entertainment Weekly</i> revealed that their sources indicated that the Aegon's Conquest prequel was \"not happening at this time.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-EW_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-EW-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On February 8, 2024, <i>The Hollywood Reporter</i> disclosed that Mattson Tomlin is attached to the project.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Tomlin_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Tomlin-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Tomlin then confirmed the report to be true on his social media account.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On April 6, 2024, Tomlin tweeted an image featuring a copy of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> captioned \"⚔️\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and replied to it with \"I've got a pretty sick job.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In July 2025, Tomlin tweeted he was still writing for the project. Tomlin also revealed that author <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> has been involved in the creation of the show.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Aegon%27s_Conquest_(TV_series)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>This page uses content from the <b><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Wiki_of_Westeros\">Wiki of Westeros</a></b>. The original content was at <b><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Aegon&#39;s_Conquest_(Mattson_Tomlin)\">Aegon's Conquest (Mattson Tomlin)</a> on the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/wiki/Wiki_of_Westeros\">Wiki of Westeros</a></b>. The list of authors can be seen in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://gameofthrones.fandom.com/index.php?title=Aegon%27s_Conquest_(Mattson_Tomlin)&amp;action=history\"><b>page history</b></a>. As with A Wiki of Ice and Fire, the content of Fandom.com is available under the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/\">CC-BY-SA License</a>.\n</p>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Tomlin-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Tomlin_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Tomlin_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Tomlin_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Hollywood Reporter: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/game-of-thrones-spinoff-aegons-conquest-mattson-tomlin-1235792104/\">‘Game of Thrones’ Aegon’s Conquest Spinoff in the Works From ‘The Batman Part II’ Writer (Exclusive)</a> (February 8, 2024)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Variety-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Variety_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Variety_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Variety: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/game-of-thrones-prequel-aegons-conquest-hbo-1235570239/\">'Game of Thrones' Prequel About Aegon's Conquest Eyed at HBO</a> (April 3, 2023)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-THR-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-THR_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The Hollywood Reporter: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-features/house-of-the-dragon-game-of-thrones-prequels-1235181929/\">Inside ‘House of the Dragon’: The Epic Mission to Make the Next ‘Game of Thrones’</a> (July 19, 2022)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-EW-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-EW_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">EW.com: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://ew.com/tv/game-of-thrones-prequel-knight-of-the-seven-kingdoms-the-hedge-knight-series-order/\">Game of Thrones prequel The Hedge Knight gets series order from HBO</a> \n(April 12, 2023)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Twitter: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://twitter.com/mattsontomlin/status/1755753186487673154\">mattson tomlin (@mattsontomlin)</a> (February 8, 2024)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Twitter: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://twitter.com/mattsontomlin/status/1776742629314859399\">mattson tomlin (@mattsontomlin)</a> (April 6, 2024)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Twitter: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://twitter.com/mattsontomlin/status/1776844899306123634\">mattson tomlin (@mattsontomlin)</a> (April 6, 2024)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Winter is Coming: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://winteriscoming.net/aegons-conquest-spinoff-writer-just-gave-updates-waiting-hear\">Aegon's Conquest spinoff writer just gave us the updates we've been waiting to hear</a> (July 31, 2025)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spac